Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: DIME PR is a small, aggressive boutique PR agency which maintains a strong emphasis on its technology practice area and specializes in working with startups and early-stage companies who can't afford to waste capital on overpriced agencies.   DIME PR puts its clients in front of the tech world's largest audiences and influencers.  Our clients are routinely featured in outlets such as: TechCrunch, Lifehacker, GigaOM, PC Magazine, PC World, NetworkWorld, CNET, and many, many more.   DIME PR believes in a full-contact approach to PR - traditional media, new media, and social media combined in one driving force to create awareness, preference, and demand.   DIME Public Relations was founded in May 2008 by Timothy R. Williams, a former senior-level marketing communications executive in the online gambling industry, a career which landed him in the Central American paradise of Costa Rica in 2003 where he continues to reside today.   Williams left the online gambling industry in 2006 after the passage of federal legislation aimed at curtailing the growth of online gambling in the United States.  Williams was hired as a Managing Director for Pop Culture PR, an award-winning consumer and lifestyle PR agency located in Los Angeles two months later.  Williams would serve full-time in his capacity as Managing Director at Pop Culture PR from his home office in Costa Rica until launching DIME PR in May of 2008. In addition to running the day-to-day operations of DIME PR, Williams continues to serve in an advisory and MD role at Pop Culture PR.

Description: Ervolina Associates is a manufacturer’s representative firm.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: In 1967, Kenneth Ervolina established his manufacturer’s representative firm by building the first network of kitchen and bath dealers in Florida focused on introducing high-end appliances into what had long been a very low-end builder market. Products like Waste King Universal, Thermador and Sub-Zero soon achieved a significant market share. In 1985, Tim joined the firm as a sales representative, focused on developing Southwest and Central Florida markets. And in 1987, Michael, who is now the CEO, joined the team and quickly developed the North East coastal market. Changes in the distribution of appliances (and the rise of big-box retailers) forced us to think about how we would respond. It meant entry into a new market—kitchen and bath cabinetry—but we knew many of the key players and our reputation as the premier Manufacturer’s Rep Agency in Florida, made the transition smoother than we had expected. In the early years, we represented cabinetry from a number of manufacturers. But a wave of mergers and acquisitions meant that several of our product lines were now owned by MasterBrand Cabinets and eventually, we became an exclusive agency for MasterBrand (the world’s largest manufacturer of kitchen and bath cabinetry). MasterBrand is a division of Fortune Brands. Today we have 9 representatives serving the retail dealer, builder and home center markets and we are proud of the efforts of this team of top-tier professionals. Fifty years after we started, we are still here, still growing and still focused on our customers first.
